6:
Mm... That smell! The Endless Blue's
cuisine really knows how to get your
attention. What an inviting aroma!
9:
You know, you become an entirely
different person when it comes to
food...
12:
Don't worry, little guy! We'll find your
mama soon! Now, say "ah!"
22:
Yes, I believe he's a Sheephird from
Palpebra...
26:
Wait, so he ain't just some needy
brat?
40:
Hey... The hell you think you're
doing? Quit staring at me and
mumbling to yourselves.
43:
We could be asking you the same
question, "kid." Why pretend to be a
brat?
48:
What I do with my time is MY
business. What do you care?
52:
Well, we were just wondering... Are
you a drifter from Palpebra?
55:
We could take you back to Palpebra
if you like.
59: Whoa, seriously? I didn't expect that...
63: Yeah, if you just come with us, we'll—
67:
Hold on, I never said anything about
going anywhere.
71:
I don't really have any reason to go
back... In fact, this place is... Well...
76:
Just spit it out, brat. We ain't got all
day.
81:
Wait... Don't tell me you want to keep
tricking girls into thinking you’re a
kid!
86: O-of course not! I-I-I would never!
96:
Sh-shut up! Just don't go blabbing
about the Sheephirds in front of—
102:
I-I dunno! I have nooo idea what
they're talking about!
106:
The Sheephirds are an ethnic group,
many of whom live in the city of
Palpebra.
109:
The defining feature of this group is
their youthful appearance. They
resemble children, even as adults.
112:
Um... Are you one of these
Sheephirds, Ruto?
113:
Wait... Wouldn't that mean... you're
actually a lot older than you look?
117:
N-n-no! I weally am a widdle
seven-year-old boy!
119:
Uh... Yeah, sure you are...
What a creep...
123:
Huh? W-wait, ladies! Come back!
Come baaack!
127:
Um... Are we supposed to apologize
here?
132:
Nah, that kid got his just deserts.
Anyway, let's get going.
141:
You! What are you doing to my
precious lady friends?!
147:
R-runt? Who the hell are you calling
a runt?!
154: Hmph. Not so tough now, are you?
158:
Don't worry, ladies! Your knight in
shining armor has saved the day!
Now, how about we get some cake
and—
162:
That was amazing! Hey, kid, wanna
join our junior squadron? The
training's tough, but it's worth it!
166:
No way! You see, I... I-I'm already
part of this group!
170: Huh? Wait, I thought you said—
175:
Lalala, I can't hear you! Now let's get
a move on!
180:
Huh?! W-wait, we never agreed to
this!
